{"_id":"422c4812639f23ca","name":"Alice's Special Tea","type":"object","img":"icons/consumables/drinks/cup-simple-earthen-brown-tan.webp","system":{"description":"A delicious tea mixed with a powerful soporific drug used by Alice Liddell, the Director of Wonder. Those who drink the tea must make a Defense Check or fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only suffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or the use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject. Alice uses this tea to incapacitate intruders and unwilling patients, offering it under the pretense of hospitality.","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"value":100,"equipped":false,"properties":["Soporific","Drugged","Requires Defense Check","Long-lasting sleep"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"14f7affb3de51794","name":"Alissa's Letters to Her Family","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-torn-brown.webp","system":{"description":"A series of increasingly terrified and delusional letters written by Alissa of Norfolk to her family during her first month at Wonder asylum. The letters describe how Wonder is 'hell on earth, where strange presences move in the dark rooms, animated by an evil will.' After the first month, the letters became more desperate until they abruptly ceased. These letters prompted the Duke of Norfolk to secretly approach the Order for help, asking the Hunters to save his daughter and shed light on the dark dealings happening in the asylum.","location":"Duke of Norfolk's possession (quest background)","importance":"important","found":true,"scenario":"wonderbedlam"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"2046c0bb8b3662f2","name":"Hatta's Time Clocks","type":"object","img":"icons/sundries/misc/clock-stopwatch-gold-black.webp","system":{"description":"Specialized clockwork devices created by Hatta Carter, the most skilled inventor in all of England. These experimental clocks can manipulate the flow of time itself. One clock can slow time (allowing Hatta to defend more effectively), while another can speed it up (allowing Hatta and his Automata to act instantly, stopping anyone's action regardless of the situation). The clocks represent Hatta's brilliant theories on automatons and physics-defying mechanics.","quantity":2,"weight":3,"value":800,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical","Time manipulation","Experimental technology","Unique invention"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"a65022c15ab45963","name":"Hatta's Wonder Blueprint","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/blueprint-axe.webp","system":{"description":"The tablecloth on Hatta Carter's tea table is actually the blueprint of Wonder drawn by the mad inventor during construction. This detailed map reveals the formula for going beyond the mirror: 'Beyond the madness, beyond the basement, beyond the mirror.' The blueprint shows the complete structure of the asylum, including passages that defy normal physics. Hatta will strongly object if anyone tries to take the map, as this would ruin his table's setting for tea.","location":"The Basement - on Hatta's tea table","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"wonderbedlam"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"cff0870fa746e075","name":"Message from the Director","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-red-white.webp","system":{"description":"A rolled-up note carried by a small white rabbit in a message holder around its neck. The message is clearly addressed to the Hunters: 'You are not welcome at Wonder, as you are not here seeking something but someone. This place welcomes only those who need healing of the mind.' The paper is signed, 'The Director'.","location":"Entrance Hall - carried by White Rabbit","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"wonderbedlam"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"f52378a99bafa608","name":"White Rabbit Message Holders","type":"clue","img":"icons/containers/bags/pouch-simple-leather-brown-red.webp","system":{"description":"Small message holders tied around the necks of the white rabbits that wander through Wonder's Cure Rooms. Each rabbit carries a cryptic clue about how to access the Basement. The messages include hints like: 'It's not always convenient to knock on a door with your hand,' 'Knocking on a door is the bare minimum to be expected of a respectable person,' and 'When you arrive at a door, it is polite to ask if anyone is home.' These clues, when understood together, reveal the formula: 'Is anyone under the house?' which opens the door painted on the floor in the Entrance Hall.","location":"Cure Rooms - carried by White Rabbits","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"wonderbedlam"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
